{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"87ddcdc4-e0bf-4c0c-817f-af1b54ebc111","content":"Build succeeds. Here's the pattern:\n\n**Before (v3):**\n```csharp\n[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]\n[TestMethod]\npublic void MyTest() { Validate(null); }\n```\n\n**After (v4):**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void MyTest() {\n    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));\n}\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` matches the **exact** type (no subclasses)\n- Use `Assert.ThrowsAsync<T>()` / `Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>()` for async methods\n- The exception is returned, so you can also assert on its `.Message` or other properties","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b498f802-cbec-4e3a-b64a-23b694ae182d","outputTokens":197,"requestId":"D001:12531F:178032E:1B91FDA:69EC2A81"},"id":"3b1ca0e3-c981-4623-b052-589243dff2f1","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:44:26.050Z","parentId":"5a257df3-491c-48ad-9523-122e0d35bdd2"}
